{
  "texts": [
    "This second step has an obvious solution: We choose µ i -ρ i when w i ≥ 0, and we choose µ i + ρ i when w i < 0.",
    "In words: For long positions the worst return is the minimum possible; for short positions the worst return is the maximum possible.",
    "With this observation, we obtain a simple formula for the worst-case portfolio mean return,",
    "The first term is the nominal mean return; the second term, which is nonpositive, gives the degradation of return induced by the uncertainty.",
    "We refer to ρ T |w| as the portfolio return forecast error penalty in our return forecast."
  ]
}